  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Hold of Passion
---
Excessive pains and pleasures are justly to be regarded as the greatest
diseases to which the soul is liable. For a man who is in great joy or in
great pain, in his unseasonable eagerness to attain the one and to avoid the
other, is not able to see or to hear anything rightly; but he is mad, and is
at the time utterly incapable of any participation in reason.
